body:
I have a list of tests that fail locally (although it may not be complete).
Enough seems to work that I think it's worth testing properly.

Only issue may be that it's pretty slow to run locally and uses a decent amount of CPU and memory.

commit.message:
Remove CYTHON_USE_ASYNC_SLOTS

It's a backport for versions that we no longer care about.

We're always able to define the async methods on classes.
It should also be possible to look them up in the limited API
(which was the only case where it wasn't defined).

GraalPython fixes taken from their patch

GraalPython maintains a patch against Cython at
https://github.com/oracle/graalpython/blob/f207af3b41b2beaa29e5698b045bd2b9c5146f20/graalpython/lib-graalpython/patches/Cython/Cython-3.0.10.patch

I've taken some of the easy fixes out of it (but not everything)
and applied them here. They all look reasonable, but I've taken
it on trust that these fixes are the right thing to do.
